replies.bodyText:
Ok. I that case I would suggest adding a check when applying the MaxMessageSize value, either not using the value at all:
                if (clientConfigProperties.getMaxMessageSize() != ClientConfigProperties.MAX_MESSAGE_SIZE_UNLIMITED) {
                    receiver.setMaxMessageSize(new UnsignedLong(clientConfigProperties.getMaxMessageSize()));
                }

or applying 0 in the "unlimited size" case, in order to not transport 18446744073709551615 on the wire.
And I would also change the exception text to max-message-size must be >= -1.

